task.summary:
Add initial project setup for ShooterGame automation and build system
- Introduced `.vsconfig` with required Visual Studio components. - Added new scripts and batch files for automated builds, packaging, and deployment. - Included build and project configuration files for Unreal Engine setup. - Implemented Gauntlet-based test harness with initial test cases.

Update `.idea` workspace settings
- Configured Git settings and integration with GitHub. - Enabled metadata file check-ins and unsaved scene checks. - Added placeholders for local tasks and commit messages.

Fix `#include` ordering across source files
- Adjusted the position of `ShooterGame.h` includes to comply with coding standards. - Ensured consistency and logical placement of headers for improved readability.

Update includes and fix compatibility issues for UE5 migration
- Replaced deprecated headers and APIs with UE5-compliant alternatives. - Added missing includes across multiple files to resolve build errors. - Adjusted header ordering for consistency and clarity.

Refactor replication graph and game instance code for clarity and compliance
- Updated use of `TWeakObjectPtr` and `TSharedRef` for safer pointer handling. - Commented out unused controller connection delegate in `ShooterGameInstance.cpp`. - Cleaned up `.idea` workspace metadata.

Update replication graph for UE 5.7 compatibility
- Replaced `TWeakObjectPtr<UNetConnection>` with raw pointer due to `UNetConnection` no longer being a UObject. - Adjusted null and validity checks for raw pointers. - Enhanced player state frequency limiter and logging methods for replication nodes.

Refactor delegate usage and input handling for UE5.7 compatibility
- Updated `FPakPlatformFile` delegates to use accessor methods and renamed delegates for clarity. - Adjusted `SimulateInputKey` to use `FInputKeyEventArgs` with updated input device parameters. - Made minor adjustments to `.idea` workspace metadata.

Refactor input handling, UI logic, and font initialization for UE5.7 compatibility
- Updated `FKey` handling to use `GetVirtualKey()` for consistency in input mappings across widgets. - Removed unnecessary `.ItemHeight` property from list widgets in multiple UI components. - Switched to `Algo::Sort` for safer and more optimal sorting in demo list. - Adjusted font macros in `ShooterStyle` to support composite fonts with lazy loading. - Added missing `LocalPlayer` and other necessary includes across several files to resolve compatibility issues.
Refactor leaderboard initialization to replace `new` with `Add` for improved clarity and safety

Update replication graph and game instance for UE5.7 compatibility
- Added `ANoPawnPlayerController` as `NotRouted` in replication graph. - Refined map name check in `ShooterGameInstance` to use short map names via `FPackageName::GetShortName`. - Minor adjustments to `.idea` workspace metadata and task settings.
Refactor bot initialization logic and map name checks in `ShooterGameInstance` and `ShooterGameMode` for improved clarity and consistency
Set `MaxBots` default value in `ShooterGameMode` and update default global game mode to `ShooterGame_Menu`.
Clamp bot count to valid range and refine quit game logic for improved stability and consistency

Update replication graph for improved UE5.7 compatibility
- Refined handling of `AlwaysRelevantStreamingLevelActors` with added null checks for safer operations. - Replaced raw pointer use with `TWeakObjectPtr` for `UNetConnection` in `FShooterAlwaysRelevantActorInfo`. - Enhanced player state initialization logic for replication nodes. - Removed outdated UE5.7-specific comments and fixed metadata inconsistencies.
Remove deprecated automation scripts, build configurations, and related files for ShooterGame

Remove platform-specific subsystems and deprecated configurations
- Removed `OnlineSubsystemPS4` and `OnlineSubsystemLive` due to deprecation. - Cleaned up unused target platforms in `ShooterGame.uproject`. - Updated `.idea` metadata and comments in `DefaultEngine.ini` for UE5 compatibility.

Update README.md for comprehensive UE5.7 project details
- Added detailed porting notes, feature highlights, and build instructions for ShooterGame's transition to UE5.7. - Documented new Lumen, Nanite, TSR, and VSM rendering technologies. - Included performance tuning options, known issues, and contribution guidelines. - Updated `.idea` and `Config/DefaultEditor.ini` for editor profile improvements.

Update `.idea`, `Config/DefaultEngine.ini`, and `Highrise_Lights.umap` for project configuration and compatibility improvements
- Enabled mesh distance fields and Nanite fallback meshes in `DefaultEngine.ini`. - Updated audio and rendering settings for optimized UE5.7 performance. - Adjusted `.idea` workspace metadata and tasks for minor project refinements. - Modified `Highrise_Lights.umap` for map-specific updates.
